values:
Just registered for the Um again.  

Those of you who know, are probably wondering why. Well you see. . . I'm crazy.  And I like to hurt myself a little.

I thought the first line of the "What you get with your entry" info was pretty much accurate. 

    * 26.2 miles of beautiful trail, plenty of hills, and passing discomfort followed by an abiding sense of accomplishment
    * The coolest CoolMax race T-shirt you will ever own
    * Goody Bag to beat all goody bags
    * Distinctive Finisher's Pint Glass (note to medal-collectors: we offer pint glasses in place of medals!)
    * Handmade awards
    * A roaring fire in the Umstead Lodge and post race festivities
    * Chances to win fabulous door prizes
    * Delicious Post-Race Meal 

Anyone care to join me?

the long run was Saturday, not today. 

in case it matters to anyone.
Ran with Ru around the lake.  Humid and threatening to rain the whole time. Did a short run before race packet pickup and lunch.

Unpacked the bags from the weekend and then grabbed Ru for a run. Did a hard surface run through the hood. Just trotted along with Ru.  Ru did a lot of pit stops. Seemingly more than normal. 

Raleigh seems really hot and muggy having just come back from the near perfect weather up in Blacksburg.
